# Remote shell configuration for tt-lang tools
# Copy this file to remote.conf and configure for your setup.
#
# REMOTE_SHELL is the command used to execute commands on the remote machine
# where tt-lang is built and tests run. All tools (run-test.sh, copy-file.sh,
# etc.) use this single command for both execution and file transfer.
#
# Examples:
#   SSH + Docker:  REMOTE_SHELL="ssh user@server docker exec -i my-container"
#   Direct SSH:    REMOTE_SHELL="ssh user@server"
#   Lima VM:       REMOTE_SHELL="limactl shell ttsim --"

REMOTE_SHELL="ssh user@server docker exec -i tt-lang"

# For Docker setups: set these for reliable file copying.
# Stdin piping can fail when sudo or other intermediaries are in the chain.
# When set, file copies use scp + docker cp instead of stdin piping.
#
# REMOTE_HOST="user@server"
# REMOTE_CONTAINER="tt-lang"
# DOCKER_SUDO=0    # Set to 1 if docker requires sudo
